FBIS4-56687 "drlat089_o_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-089 Daily Report 7 May 1994 Colombia Attorney General Opposes Court's Drug Ruling Attorney General Opposes Court's Drug Ruling PA0705021394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal A Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 7 May 94 PA0705021394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal A Network Spanish BFN [From the "Seven O'Clock Newscast"] [Text] Attorney General Carlos Gustavo Arrieta's strong opposition to the Constitutional Court's recent decision has apparently weakened the legal arguments supporting the approval of the personal drug dose. [Begin Arrieta recording] I disagree with the ruling, which I think is capable of creating complex legal, moral, social, and international problems in the country. In terms of the law, such a broad interpretation of personal freedom could create distortions that have no place in this government. We will soon find ourselves debating other social issues, such as euthanasia or suicide. Let us keep in mind that personal freedom cannot be extended to a point at which it harms society. [end recording]
